// FD-004 #2: empty single-line `If` body forms must emit E0215 and not panic.
// Inputs in this fixture are explicitly single-line shapes (anything ending
// in a bare `Then` followed by a newline is block form, exercised by
// parser_if.cb already).

// `Then` immediately followed by `:` — empty then-body, second statement is the real one.
If x > 0 Then : a = 1

// `Then Else` — empty then-body, else-body present.
If z > 0 Then Else b = 2

// `Else :` — empty else-body, valid Then. The recovered `c = 3` is the
// then-body; nothing in the else.
If w > 0 Then c = 3 Else :
